"{\"uid\": \"columbiatribune.com-story-lifestyle-2024-07-17-before-the-summer-olympics-trek-through-ancient-and-underwater-paris-74408163007\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Editor's note: This is the first in a series of five columns revolving around the Summer Olympics in Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 101, \"end\": 106, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When we think of Paris, the Eiffel Tower, the Louvre, and bustling cafes likely come to mind.\", \"from\": 109, \"to\": 202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 126, \"end\": 131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 155, \"end\": 161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.9976167072888009, \"rank\": 0.0023889863650707606, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But have you ever wondered what this famous city looked like millions of years ago?\", \"from\": 203, \"to\": 286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us take a journey through the natural history of Paris, exploring how the land was formed, what creatures once roamed here, and how it evolved into the vibrant city we know today.\", \"from\": 288, \"to\": 471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 341, \"end\": 346, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"About 45 million years ago, during the Eocene Epoch, the area that is now Paris was dramatically different from the big city we know today.\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 612, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 547, \"end\": 552, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead of a city, it was a very warm shallow sea.\", \"from\": 613, \"to\": 663, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This ancient sea was full of life, and was like an underwater natural city itself.\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 746, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Diving beneath the surface were a variety of marine creatures.\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 810, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Schools of fish darted through the water while long-necked Plesiosaurs and sharks swam through looking for prey.\", \"from\": 811, \"to\": 923, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Coral reefs, much like those found in tropical oceans today, provided shelter and food for many organisms.\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 1030, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Crustaceans scurried along the sea floor, and ancient crabs and lobsters hid in the coral and rocks.\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1131, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Over millions of years, the remains of these marine organisms, along with sand and other sediments, settled on the sea floor.\", \"from\": 1133, \"to\": 1258, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As layer after layer of sediment accumulated, the pressure from the weight above compressed them into limestone.\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1371, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This process, known as lithification, created the foundation of what would much later become Paris.\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1472, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1466, \"end\": 1471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today, this limestone is not only what the city sits on, but it was used to build many of the historic buildings of Paris.\", \"from\": 1473, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1589, \"end\": 1594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Missouri shares a similar geologic story with Paris, as it was also built by a foundation of limestone deposited in an ancient shallow sea that covered what is now Missouri.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1597, \"end\": 1605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_River\", \"score\": 0.9999999999504325, \"rank\": 4.9712076000632895e-11, \"text\": \"Missouri\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_River\"}, {\"begin\": 1643, \"end\": 1648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1761, \"end\": 1769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_River\", \"score\": 0.9999999999504325, \"rank\": 4.9712076000632895e-11, \"text\": \"Missouri\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_River\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Missouri_River\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This sea was home to a diverse range of marine life, including brachiopods, trilobites, and crinoids, whose remains contributed to the sediment that would eventually form limestone.\", \"from\": 1771, \"to\": 1952, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Back to Paris - the land began to gradually rise over millions of years.\", \"from\": 1954, \"to\": 2026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1962, \"end\": 1967, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By the time the Pleistocene Epoch rolled around about 2.6 million years ago, the landscape was dramatically different.\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2145, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2043, \"end\": 2054, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quaternary_glaciation\", \"score\": 0.9988676759741782, \"rank\": 0.0011336076371738656, \"text\": \"Pleistocene\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quaternary_glaciation\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quaternary_glaciation\"}, {\"begin\": 2055, \"end\": 2060, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geologic_time_scale\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.4941997050125356e-24, \"text\": \"Epoch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geologic_time_scale\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geologic_time_scale\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The area was shaped by the movement of glaciers, which carved out valleys and left behind fertile soils.\", \"from\": 2146, \"to\": 2250, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This is how the land we know came to be, but it wasn't time for humans just yet.\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2332, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And that's probably a good thing as it was awfully frozen!\", \"from\": 2333, \"to\": 2391, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Before humans ever set foot in Paris, woolly mammoths, saber-toothed cats, and giant deer roamed the land.\", \"from\": 2393, \"to\": 2499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2424, \"end\": 2429, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the climate warmed and the Ice Age ended, forests began to spread across the area, providing a habitat for many more familiar-looking animals that we can still see in some areas today.\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2687, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Humans did not arrive in Paris until about 12,000 years ago.\", \"from\": 2689, \"to\": 2749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2714, \"end\": 2719, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These early inhabitants were hunter-gatherers who lived off the land, hunting animals and gathering fruits and nuts from the forests.\", \"from\": 2750, \"to\": 2883, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As time passed, these nomadic tribes began to settle, and agricultural practices started.\", \"from\": 2884, \"to\": 2973, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was just the start of the next major shift in the Paris landscape.\", \"from\": 2974, \"to\": 3045, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3029, \"end\": 3034, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By around 250 B.C., a Celtic tribe known as the Parisii established a settlement on the \\u00cele de la Cit\\u00e9, an island in the middle of the Seine River.\", \"from\": 3047, \"to\": 3194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3061, \"end\": 3065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\", \"score\": 0.9999999545193542, \"rank\": 4.548079070961641e-08, \"text\": \"B.C.\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anno_Domini\"}, {\"begin\": 3069, \"end\": 3075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celts\", \"score\": 0.9999999993815436, \"rank\": 6.078046149923529e-10, \"text\": \"Celtic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celts\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celts\"}, {\"begin\": 3095, \"end\": 3102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parisii_(Gaul)\", \"score\": 0.8453571329680546, \"rank\": 0.17142857142856688, \"text\": \"Parisii\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parisii_(Gaul)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Parisii_(Gaul)\"}, {\"begin\": 3135, \"end\": 3149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00cele_de_la_Cit\\u00e9\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"\\u00cele de la Cit\\u00e9\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00cele_de_la_Cit\\u00e9\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/\\u00cele_de_la_Cit\\u00e9\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This was the beginning of human influence on the landscape, setting the stage for the city we know today.\", \"from\": 3195, \"to\": 3300, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, there were many human influences before Paris became what we know now - but that's a story for another day.\", \"from\": 3302, \"to\": 3418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3351, \"end\": 3356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So as you watch the Summer Olympics, take a few minutes to imagine the prehistoric sea creatures swimming where buildings now stand, and the woolly mammoths roaming the land that is now paved with human-packed streets and buildings.\", \"from\": 3420, \"to\": 3652, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mike Szydlowski is a science teacher and zoo facilitator at Jefferson STEAM School.\", \"from\": 3654, \"to\": 3737, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3714, \"end\": 3723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1153992752043328e-18, \"text\": \"Jefferson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Jefferson\"}, {\"begin\": 3724, \"end\": 3729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/STEAM_fields\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.114464125194274e-21, \"text\": \"STEAM\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/STEAM_fields\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/STEAM_fields\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TIME FOR A POP QUIZ  How did the limestone that Paris sits on form?\", \"from\": 3739, \"to\": 3806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3787, \"end\": 3792, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What kinds of marine life lived in the shallow sea that once covered Paris?\", \"from\": 3808, \"to\": 3883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3877, \"end\": 3882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How did the movement of glaciers shape the landscape of Paris?\", \"from\": 3885, \"to\": 3947, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3941, \"end\": 3946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why was it beneficial that humans did not arrive in Paris until after the Ice Age ended?\", \"from\": 3949, \"to\": 4037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4001, \"end\": 4006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What marked the beginning of human influence on the landscape of Paris?\", \"from\": 4039, \"to\": 4110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4104, \"end\": 4109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999386091, \"rank\": 6.11670336132543e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"LAST WEEK'S QUIZ ANSWERS  Why are scientists worried about the current hurricane season?\", \"from\": 4112, \"to\": 4200, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Scientists are concerned because the ocean temperatures are much warmer than normal and that might lead to earlier and more severe hurricanes.\", \"from\": 4202, \"to\": 4344, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How do warming oceans contribute to the formation and intensity of hurricanes?\", \"from\": 4346, \"to\": 4424, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Warming oceans absorb over 90% of the excess heat from global warming.\", \"from\": 4426, \"to\": 4496, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This heat increases sea surface temperatures which, when rising above 80\\u00b0 F, provide the necessary energy to fuel hurricanes.\", \"from\": 4497, \"to\": 4622, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What made Hurricane Beryl significant?\", \"from\": 4624, \"to\": 4662, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hurricane Beryl was the most powerful hurricane ever recorded this early in the Atlantic hurricane season.\", \"from\": 4664, \"to\": 4770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What are the economic implications of the increasing frequency and intensity of hurricanes?\", \"from\": 4772, \"to\": 4863, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Annual hurricane damage costs now exceed $500 billion a year.\", \"from\": 4865, \"to\": 4926, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This includes the cost of repairing homes and infrastructure, as well as rising insurance premiums.\", \"from\": 4927, \"to\": 5026, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How can improved forecasting models help mitigate the impacts of stronger hurricanes?\", \"from\": 5028, \"to\": 5113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Improved forecasting models can predict the path and intensity of hurricanes more accurately.\", \"from\": 5115, \"to\": 5208, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, while these measures can help save lives, they do not reduce the financial costs associated with more frequent and intense hurricanes.\", \"from\": 5209, \"to\": 5352, \"entities\": []}]}"